defaultFor all types of 
defaultincident or disruptive events Gatwick Airport Limited has a well-developed command and control structure. This is modeled on the three tier structure of Gold (strategic), Silver (tactical) and Bronze (operational). The three tier command and control model 
defaultis well understood and regularly rehearsed
default. 
default3.2
default&#xa0; 
defaultAs part of this structure, Gatwick has an Airport Snow Plan. Th
defaulte
default aim of this plan is to 
defaultdeal with the 
defaultimpact of snow and ice in a professional manner, with a clear and constant focus on minimising disruption and inconvenience to airline 
defaultpassengers. In
default order to minimise risks, Gatwick works closely with our airlines
default and their
default handling agents
default, NATs
default and other
default airport partners. Throughout any disruption we are dedicated to the welfare of passengers and the provision of timely communications to airport users and external audiences.
