defaultConclusiondefault&#xa0;default7.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe safety of passengers and airport
default 
defaultusers will always be our main priority during any adverse weather 
defaultconditions. 
default 
default7.2
default&#xa0; 
defaultSince the severe weather of 2009-2010 Gatwick has put in a place a series of measures, investing over £8m, in order to minimise any disruption. 
default7.3
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe winter period 2012-2013 saw widespread snowfall across the South East; however as a result of the processes
default in place, Gatwick was able to remain open throughout this period.
default7.4
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe believe that Heathrow needs to develop a more robust approach to its winter resilience and that it should look directly at how to limit the overscheduling of flights during the winter months. 
default 
default7.5
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe are confident 
defaultthat
default 
defaultwe have the correct structures in pla
defaultce to continue to uphold the highest of standards when dealing with adverse weather. 
default7.6
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe will continue to review any adverse weather events to ensure that we are aware or lessons learnt in order to shape future planning and preparation. 
