defaultAppendix AdefaultLondon Gatwick Weather StatesdefaultWEATHER STATE 1: Met Office forecast snow in the next seven days but not expected to accumulate. No disruption to the 
defaultoperation of the Airfield predicted.
defaultWEATHER STATE 2: Met Office 
defaultforecast snow in the next seven days and expected to accumulate which may cause disruption to the
default operation of
default airfield
defaultWEATHER STATE 3: Met Office forecast snow in the next 24 hours and expected to accumulate which may cause disruption to the
default operation of
default airfield
defaultWEATHER STATE 4: 
defaultMet Office forecast snow in the next 2 hours and expected to accumulate which may cause disruption to the operation of the Airfield.
defaultWEATHER STATE 5: 
defaultSnow is falling and accumulating but NOT likely to lead to airfield disruption 
defaultand can be safely and efficiently managed by the Airfield Operations team.
defaultWEATHER STATE 6: Snow is falling and accumulating in sufficient amounts to cause disruption to the 
defaultoperation of 
defaultairfield
defaultWEATHER STATE 7: 
defaultSnow has stopped falling and accumulating w
defaultith no further accumulations forecast, but snow clearing duties continue on the Airfield and/or the operation of the Airport is being disrupted.
